data.title: Surprisingly good newcomer restaurant
data.text: Genuinely good Mexican food. I like to try out any new restaurants, in the past six months I had Mexican food at El Comal. The food was fresh and very tasty.

data.title: El Comal!
data.text: El Comal is a little Quaint  Mexican Restaurant on 3rd Avenue in the heart of Downtown Chula Vista. The Authentic Mexican Food is very good! The service was excellent!

data.title: Interesting Menu
data.text: The El Comal menu has all the standard items, plus many interesting specials. We had the chile relleno with crema; it was topped with pomegranate seeds. It was very good, and different. The flan was absolutely wonderful. The place was full for lunch on a Thursday, as it should be. The service is friendly and pleasant. We will be returning !

data.title: Great homestyle eatery...family friendly!
data.text: This is a small mexican restaurant that offers up some great daily specials and authentic food. It is family friendly and play some great mexican music while dining. On Saturday nights, we have dined as a family ( i have 2 kids, ages 3 and 5) and we enjoyed live mariachi music.  On my husbands bday, they gave him a free flan with a candle on top and played "Las Mananitas", which is the mexican version of happy birthday. It was wonderful!

data.title: Muy rico sason // Good food
data.text:
Tienen muy buen sason... me gusto mucho las enchiladas suizas y el agua de horchata tambien tiene muy rico sabor mi única sugerencia es de que pueden hacer las tirillas un poco más delgadas. Definitivamente regresaré a comer aquí 

The flavors of thaf food are really good. I had the enchiladas suizas with some orchata. My only advice is that the hands made tortillas could be done a bit thinner. Overall i will finally will come back
